<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.199347>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. The advertisement call of Leptolalax aereus sp. nov. holotype SAMA R 64236, recorded at ambient air temperature of 22.4 ºC (A) 25 s waveform of relative amplitude, (B) an expanded 0.7 s waveform, and (C) corresponding 0.7 s spectrogram showing two representative calls, and (D) a power spectrum (relative amplitude vs. frequency). The advertisement call of Leptolalax aereus sp. nov. paratype NCMS 76068, recorded at 25.5 ºC. (E) 25 s waveform of relative amplitude, (F) an expanded 0.7 s waveform, and (G) corresponding 0.7 s spectrogram showing three representative calls, and (H) power spectrum (relative amplitude vs. frequency)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/199347/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.199348>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Temperature-dependence of the average dominant frequency of the advertisement call of Leptolalax aereus sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/199348/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

